parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates without driver input
sudden and unexpected acceleration
inability to control the vehicle's speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctioning windows and accessories can cause distractions while driving, potentially leading to accidents, and may also lead to water damage or theft if windows are stuck in the down position.
symptoms: Windows roll down or up on their own
windows fail to roll up or down
accessories (such as sunroof) malfunction
electrical system faults.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Ignition System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities. Ignition system failure can also lead to catalytic converter damage, resulting in costly repairs.
symptoms: Engine rough idling
engine stalling
jerking motion before stalling
no warning lights or indicators
electrical shorts in ignition wires
damage to catalytic converters.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Airbags to Deploy in Frontal Collisions
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in frontal collisions can result in serious injuries or fatalities, as the vehicle's safety features are compromised.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in frontal collisions
even at moderate speeds
resulting in injuries to occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power window motor can cause the windows to malfunction, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks, especially in emergency situations.
symptoms: Windows will not go up or down
humming sound when operating the windows
windows stuck in a particular position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The shattering of the rear quarter panel glass can cause injury to occupants, especially in the event of a collision, and may also lead to water ingress and damage to the vehicle's interior.
symptoms: Rear quarter panel glass shatters
especially in the event of a collision
water ingress into the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS brake system can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to increased stopping distances, loss of control, and accidents, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes directly to the floor
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
the vehicle pulls to one side when braking
the ABS warning light is illuminated on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Warped Front Brake Disc Rotors and Pads
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped front brake disc rotors and pads can cause the brakes to vibrate, pulsate, or grab, leading to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and accidents, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal pulsates or vibrates when applied
the vehicle pulls to one side when braking
the brakes make a grinding or screeching noise
the brake rotors are excessively worn or warped.
